d at later epochs in the disks. On the other hand, 10-5 to 10-4 m\naggregates are continuously pushed outward during the evolution of the solar\nnebula. Our simulations suggest that irrespective of the employed solar nebula\nmodel, photophoresis is a mechanism that can explain the presence of hot\ntemperature minerals in the formation region of comets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 May 2011 12:54:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
